                <div id=3D"section1">
                    <div class=3D"unit">
                        <h3>Bayes' Theorem</h3>
                        <p>
                            Suppose that on your most recent visit to the
                            doctor's office, you decide to get tested for a=
 rare
                            disease. If you are unlucky enough to receive a
                            positive result, the logical next question is,
                            "Given the test result, what is the probability=
 that
                            I actually have this disease?" (Medical tests a=
re,
                            after all, not perfectly accurate.) Bayes' Theo=
rem
                            tells us exactly how to compute this probabilit=
y:
                        </p>

